          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-copy-1713857797107-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Return the pan to a medium-high heat and once hot, add the <strong>chopped shallot </strong>and<strong> sliced pepper </strong>and cook for 2-3 min or until beginning to soften</p><p>Once softened, add 2/3 of the <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>garlic </strong>(save the rest for later!) and the <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>ginger</strong> to the pan with your <strong>curry powder </strong>and <strong>ground turmeric</strong></p><p>Cook for 1 min or until fragrant</p><p>Tip: Add a drizzle more oil if your pan is looking a little dry!</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-copy-1713857801747-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-copy-1713857801747-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-copy-1713857801747-x700.jpg",
