          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-copy-1713857810853-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Whilst the rice is cooking, roll your <strong>lime[s]</strong> with your hand on a hard surface (to release more juice) and cut in half</p><p>Once cooked, add the juice of <strong>half </strong>the <strong>lime</strong> into the rice<strong> </strong>and mix to combine – this is your <strong>garlic & lime rice</strong></p><p>Cut the <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>lime</strong> into 1 wedge per person</p><p>Once the meatballs are cooked, mix <strong>half</strong> your <strong>cultured</strong> <strong>coconut</strong> through the sauce – this is your <strong>fiery jerk-spiced pork meatball curry</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
